<p>GDP growth: 7.2% GDP: $19bn (PPP: $32bn) Inflation: 3.2% Population: 32.0m GDP per head: $590 (PPP: $1,020)</p>

<p>The president, Hamid Karzai, will be severely constrained by the need to repay the loyalty of powerful groups whose backing secured him re-election. The Taliban will harry the regime, and attacks will be frequent and bloody and will include key international targets. There will be slow but measurable progress on economic development and reform, and several new foreign-investment projects will break ground.</p>

